Attributions
------------------------------------------------------------------------------

MLXServe is a native-Swift port of serving capabilities (continuous/batched
decode and a tiered prefix KV cache) whose design derives from:

  * oMLX — https://github.com/jundot/omlx
    Copyright (c) jundot. Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0.
    MLXServe's serving architecture (block-based chain-hash KV cache, hot RAM +
    cold SSD tiers, copy-on-write prefix sharing, the scheduler/driving contract)
    is a Swift re-implementation of oMLX's approach. oMLX itself began from
    vllm-mlx (below).

  * vllm-mlx — https://github.com/waybarrios/vllm-mlx
    The paged-KV lineage that oMLX built upon.

The batched-decode mechanism (ragged causal mask, BatchKVCache merge, prompt
cache serialization) follows, and is re-implemented from, MIT-licensed sources:

  * mlx-lm — https://github.com/ml-explore/mlx-lm  (MIT)
  * mlx-engine (disk-chunked KV + continuous batching, PR #326)
    https://github.com/lmstudio-ai/mlx-engine  (MIT)

Built on:

  * MLX / mlx-swift — https://github.com/ml-explore/mlx-swift  (MIT)
    Apple's array framework and its Swift bindings.

MLXServe is not affiliated with or endorsed by any of the above projects.
